---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';

export const title = "Kittery Dispensary Guide";
---

<Layout 
  title="Kittery Dispensary Guide | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Complete guide to opening a cannabis dispensary in Kittery, Maine. Market analysis, regulations, and investment requirements."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500916434205-0c77489c6cf7?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200&h=400"
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Kittery Dispensary Guide</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">How to open a cannabis dispensary in Kittery, Maine</p>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>Kittery, Maine's southernmost town with 10,000+ residents, is located at the border of New Hampshire, just minutes from Portsmouth. Known for its famous outlets, beautiful beaches, and historic maritime heritage, Kittery offers cannabis entrepreneurs a unique opportunity to serve both Maine residents and New Hampshire visitors in a thriving commercial district. Before moving forward, familiarize yourself with the <a href="/guides/maine-cannabis-real-estate/">real estate requirements</a> essential for success.</p>
    </section>

    <Callout title="Kittery: A Local Opportunity" type="passion">
      Operating in Kittery is more than just a business; it's about becoming a pillar of the community. Focus on local engagement and education to build lasting trust with your neighbors.
    </Callout>


    <section>
      <h2>Why Kittery?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>New Hampshire Border</strong> - Access to NH customers</li>
        <li><strong>Famous Outlets</strong> - Major shopping destination</li>
        <li><strong>Tourism Traffic</strong> - Beach and outlet shoppers</li>
        <li><strong>Very Low Competition</strong> - Prime opportunity</li>
        <li><strong>Historic Character</strong> - Quaint Maine town</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Kittery Market</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Factor</th><th>Assessment</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Population</td><td>10,000+</td></tr>
          <tr><td>NH Market Access</td><td>500,000+ nearby</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Competition</td><td>Very Low</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Real Estate</td><td>Moderate ($16-24/sq ft)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Access</td><td>I-95, Route 1</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Local Regulations</h2>
      <p>Under <a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/rules" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Maine OCP regulations</a>, Kittery operators must:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Obtain state license from Maine Office of Cannabis Policy</li>
        <li>Verify local zoning compliance</li>
        <li>Complete all compliance requirements</li>
        <li>Obtain employee authorizations</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Best Locations</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Route 1</strong> - High traffic commercial</li>
        <li><strong>Near Outlets</strong> - Shopping traffic</li>
        <li><strong>Downtown</strong> - Historic district</li>
        <li><strong>Beach Areas</strong> - Summer visitors</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Investment Requirements</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Category</th><th>Estimated Cost</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Real Estate (lease)</td><td>$2,500-4,500/mo</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Build-out</td><td>$80,000-140,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Total <a href="/guides/maine-dispensary-costs/">Investment</a></td><td>$340,000-600,000</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Success Tips</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Target New Hampshire market (no legal cannabis there)</li>
        <li>Leverage outlet traffic</li>
        <li>Beach-seasonal marketing</li>
        <li>Quality over quantity positioning</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Further Reading</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/rules" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Maine Cannabis Rules</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em>This is for informational purposes only and does not constitute legal or financial advice. Consult with qualified professionals.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
</style>
